    "description": "Asus apparently hates display bezel as much as we do, which is why its new 2018 ZenBooks have almost none. With a massively reduced footprint, the new 14-inch ZenBook is now smaller than the old 13-inch ZenBook, while the new ZenBook 13 is a tiny bijou of a laptop. With prices starting from $899, these are the affordable members of Asus' high-end laptop line.  Subscribe:   Like The Verge on Facebook:  Follow on Twitter:  Follow on Instagram:  Read More:  Community guidelines:   Subscribe to Verge Science on YouTube, a new home base for our explorations into the future of science:",
